JMC Notes 0618

- Keep layouts as dynamic as possible.  Be careful with margin, padding, position:absolute
- Layout tip: use percentages for layout (responsive design)
- Github: RefactorU/student-sample-code
- rgba(255,50,25,0.9).  The last value is opacity
- a float will collapse the default width.  Must specify the width
- block formatting context: ("The Clearfix")
*** scenarios: float, display:inline-block, position:fixed|absolute, overflow:*(except visible)
*** effects: 1) ?  2) always contains other floats and full margin box
- Bad practice: layout dependencies, tightly coupled layout design.  Creates fragile code...
- Margin collapse: siblings, parent-child
- Default image display is "inline"
